contributions.title: Songbirds By The Stream
contributions.notes:
Follow an easy flowing stream into the heart of the forest and discover the magical melodies of over 30 songbirds.
Presented in surround sound, Dan Gibson's superb digital field recordings reveal a tranquil world of warblers, thrushes, sparrows and many other delightful species.
This continuous play album offers 23 separate tracks that allow for easy access to preferred sections. Tracklist is a listing of the species featured in each track. Some of the wildlife that can be heard in the background is identified in parenthesis.
Listening instructions: For the most relaxing effect, this album should be played in a quiet atmosphere with the volume and tone controls set at a moderate level that is in keeping with nature's ambience. 
This album was later re-issued as 'Birdsong II' in the same series.
